.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn bswap16 ,
.Fn bswap32 ,
and
.Fn bswap64
functions return a byte order swapped integer.
On big endian systems, the number is converted to little endian
byte order.
On little endian systems, the number is converted to big endian
byte order.
.Pp
The
.Fn be16enc ,
.Fn be16dec ,
.Fn be32enc ,
.Fn be32dec ,
.Fn be64enc ,
.Fn be64dec ,
.Fn le16enc ,
.Fn le16dec ,
.Fn le32enc ,
.Fn le32dec ,
.Fn le64enc ,
and
.Fn le64dec
functions encode and decode integers to/from byte strings on
any alignment in big/little endian format.
.Sh HISTORY
The encode/decode functions first appeared in FreeBSD 5.1.
